formatted_address: 755 Chai Chee Rd, #05-25 Viva Business Park, Singapore 469025
name: Bai Nian Niang Dou Fu

reviews.text:
Golden Prawn Pancake ($5.90) – Crispy, golden-brown, and served piping hot, with just the right amount of greasiness. The umami, savoury flavours complemented its crispy yet bouncy texture, making it a superb dish.

Bai Nian Yong Tau Foo ($5.90) – A hearty bowl of silky bee hoon, homemade prawn paste balls, egg tofu, white stick, gold stick, and bitter gourd in a rich, savoury soup topped with spring onions. The ingredients were bouncy and juicy, though the soup was slightly salty and high in MSG. Still, a comforting and affordable meal.

Have not been eating at this location for a while was transferred back and this is the second times this week patronising this stall. Overall the food is ok but price a bit high. Customer services rendered can be improved.
One of the best yong tau foo at reasonable price. The soup is nice and easy on the palate and that secret ying yang souce is to die for. Ask for extra meehoo at no extra cost.

Generally tasty Yong tau fu. $5.90 for basic bowl.
All ingredients tasted well. Just the prawn ball getting smaller and less prawn flesh compared to last time. Finished all the soup, a little bit thirsty after that.

Standard single configuration yong tau foo beehoon soup main. Makes a hearty meal. Find this particular foodcourt to be dim and mildly uncomfortable for its unusually high humidity. A little out of the way to get to, but this is a commercial building afterall and serves a regular lunch crowd. Give it a try.

vicinity: 755 Chai Chee Road, #05-25 Viva Business Park
